title: Let's Enjoy Math with Barky the Dog
subTitle: Children want to know whether a large desk can pass through the doorway of the classroom. Numbler makes the desk immovable, but Barky shows them how to compare lengths and widths by using a ribbon.

title: Take Tech
subTitle: Takes a look into how the barcodes can convey the information to the scanner.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Train Cruise
subTitle: Criss-crossing Japan by rail. Enjoy the amazing diversity of nature and scenery throughout the country and across the four seasons. Exploring both well-known and hidden parts Japan.

title: Dining with the Chef Mini
subTitle: The techniques, ingredients and harmony of Japanese food recipes in just five minutes. Chef Rika cooks alongside master chef Tatsuo Saito to show viewers how to prepare delicious Japanese dishes at home.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Magical Japanese
subTitle: The Japanese language is rich in words and expressions influenced by nature, history, and culture. A look at the unique world of the Japanese language, accompanied with scenes from Japan.

title: The Seasons of Yamato
subTitle: A series of poetic videos by Koichi Hozan, a videographer living in Nara, in collaboration with a pianist, Mine Kawakami, for which she plays exclusive pieces, representing each season.

title: NHK World Japan
subTitle: A look at the rich and fascinating Edo era of Japan, which was dominated by a deep love for the arts. The traditional woodblock prints called Ukiyo-e blossomed during this period of time.

title: Grand Sumo Highlights
subTitle: Sumo highlights from a range of tournaments that have taken place across the globe. Sumo is one of the most traditional Japanese sports and boasts a history going back more than 1500 years.

title: Magical Japanese
subTitle: An exploration of the unique culture behind words that are related to the number seven.

title: MATSURI: The Heartbeat of Japan
subTitle: Onomichi Betcha is a three-day festival in Hiroshima Prefecture. Masked figures carry sticks with which to torment spectators. But being hit or poked with a stick is said to bring good luck.

title: Sumopedia
subTitle: Sumopedia enriches your sumo experience with information on the techniques, traditions and famous wrestlers of the past. The rules may be simple but there is a lot more to sumo than meets the eye.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: NHK World Selection
subTitle: A selection of acclaimed programmes plucked straight from NHK's domestic catalogue of channels dubbed into English.

title: BOSAI: Science That Can Save Your Life
subTitle: In Japan, extremely powerful lightning known as a superbolt can occur in the Hokuriku region during winter. What is the source of this power, which is comparable to a small nuclear explosion?

title: Design Museum Japan
subTitle: Tagawa investigates the process of design by looking at the work of Yanagi Sori, who shaped products by making models using different materials.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Fading Homeland
subTitle: As battles with Russia persist in an eastern Ukrainian town, electricity is vital. Through power grid workers risking their lives to fix the grid, we depict people losing their homeland to war.
